The paper deals with robotics and learning, which suggests that it belongs to the cs.RO (Robotics) category. The use of data-driven learning and self-supervised paradigms suggests that it could also belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) category. The use of sensors and measurement of success/failure suggests that it could belong to the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) category. The focus on grasping and object recognition suggests that it could belong to the cs.CV (Computer Vision) category. Finally, the mention of improved performance suggests that it could belong to the cs.SY (Systems and Control) category.
